I'll also plug a class you all should definitely take:

PHIL 1.08 taught by Prof. James Binkoski is offered 24F during the 10 timeslot, and I am inclined to call it a layup. The class basically delves into different theories of how time moves/flows and whether the past, present, and future exists according to the different theories, as well as if/how time travel is possible. You'll learn to evaluate these different theories via discussions and short weekly papers (which are super easy, the prof literally tells you how to write them and you can literally copy what he says in class on the papers), and you'll find that a lot of sci-fi media are flawed in the ways they portray time and time travel. There are technically readings but I'd say they are optional because the prof covers all the concepts in class anyway. The class is good for those who need to meet the TMV distrib but are inclined towards sciencey, but it's not so technical that non-science people won't be able to follow along and have fun. Additionally, the class is NRO-eligible. I took this class 23F and really enjoyed it, and the class is pretty popular among upperclassmen as well. It's an introductory class without any prereqs, so you don't need to come in with any prior knowledge. 

If you want to learn more about the class, shoot me your questions!
